Now you.

08:25.797 --> 08:27.049
Have you met me?

08:31.929 --> 08:33.013
Stupid Poopy-Bot.

08:34.806 --> 08:36.015
Jessie.

08:36.683 --> 08:37.934
I made my bed,

08:37.976 --> 08:39.270
did my homework,

08:39.270 --> 08:40.562
and cleaned my closet.

08:40.604 --> 08:41.668
Is there anything else

08:41.669 --> 08:42.731
you want me to do?

08:45.067 --> 08:46.235
Oh, oh,

08:46.236 --> 08:47.403
the silent treatment.

08:47.445 --> 08:49.321
- Well, two can play
- at that game.

08:52.116 --> 08:53.700
- I don't want to
- play that game!

08:54.868 --> 08:56.454
- Just be mad!
- Yell at me.

08:57.496 --> 08:58.623
I'm not mad

08:58.624 --> 08:59.748
at you, okay, Zuri.

09:00.916 --> 09:02.501
I'm just disappointed.

09:02.542 --> 09:04.002
- Military Mary
- meant a lot to me,

09:04.044 --> 09:05.045
And what you did

09:05.046 --> 09:06.046
really hurt my feelings.

09:09.841 --> 09:12.511
I didn't mean to hurt her.

09:12.552 --> 09:13.846
I hate to say

09:13.847 --> 09:15.139
I told you so, but...

09:15.180 --> 09:16.807
Oh, who am I kidding?

09:16.848 --> 09:18.767
Actually, I quite enjoy it.

09:20.227 --> 09:21.812
This is terrible.

09:21.853 --> 09:23.293
And no amount

09:23.294 --> 09:24.731
of chocolate poop

09:21.853 --> 09:24.731
can make it better.

09:26.984 --> 09:28.360
Doesn't hurt, though.

09:33.031 --> 09:34.408
(SALSA MUSIC PLAYING)

09:34.450 --> 09:35.618
Bertram, clean up

09:35.619 --> 09:36.785
that footwork,

09:37.702 --> 09:39.538
straighten your frame,

09:40.414 --> 09:42.416
and tuck in your butt!

09:42.458 --> 09:44.376
If I could, I would!

09:44.418 --> 09:45.919
(MUSIC STOPS)

09:45.961 --> 09:47.546
I keep hearing this

09:47.547 --> 09:49.131
voice in my head

09:45.961 --> 09:49.131
saying I can't do this.

09:49.173 --> 09:50.882
Oh, just ignore it.

09:50.924 --> 09:51.800
- That's what we do
- when we hear your voice,

09:50.924 --> 09:51.924
Right?

09:53.344 --> 09:54.532
(GRUNTS)

09:54.533 --> 09:55.720
I give up!

09:55.762 --> 09:56.889
Bertram, do you ever

09:56.890 --> 09:58.015
want to get a girlfriend?

09:58.056 --> 09:59.475
You've already been

09:59.476 --> 10:00.892
alone for like 70 years.

10:03.270 --> 10:05.001
All right.

10:05.002 --> 10:06.731
I'll do it for Salma.

10:06.773 --> 10:07.963
The only thing missing

10:07.964 --> 10:09.151
is the perfect outfit.

10:09.193 --> 10:10.548
And while I'm at it,

10:10.549 --> 10:11.903
I'll try to find something

10:09.193 --> 10:11.903
for you, too, Bertram!

10:13.738 --> 10:14.979
- (MUSIC STARTS)
- Keep dancing.

10:16.575 --> 10:17.868
(SIGHS)

10:22.080 --> 10:23.790
- I hate this
- more than you do.

10:23.832 --> 10:25.501
- I find that
- hard to believe.

10:28.795 --> 10:29.838
Believe it.

10:34.301 --> 10:35.301
Hey, Sneed.

10:36.387 --> 10:38.680
I want Military Mary back,

10:38.722 --> 10:40.474
so I'll make you an offer

10:40.475 --> 10:42.226
you can't refuse, see?

10:43.394 --> 10:44.769
Play your cards right

10:44.811 --> 10:46.251
and we both walk away

10:46.252 --> 10:47.689
from this, see?

10:50.025 --> 10:51.548
She loves

10:51.549 --> 10:53.070
gangster movies.

10:53.111 --> 10:54.134
I'll give you

10:54.135 --> 10:55.155
the same answer

10:53.111 --> 10:55.155
I gave my mother

10:55.197 --> 10:56.261
when she asked me

10:56.262 --> 10:57.324
to move out... No!

10:59.201 --> 11:00.911
There you guys are!

11:00.952 --> 11:02.638
- You know you're not - supposed to leave
- The penthouse without me.

11:02.662 --> 11:04.894
I came to trade

11:04.895 --> 11:07.125
my best toys to get

11:02.662 --> 11:07.125
Military Mary back for you.

11:07.167 --> 11:08.774
Oh, that's

11:08.775 --> 11:10.379
so sweet, Zuri.

11:10.421 --> 11:11.609
What's your excuse?

11:11.610 --> 11:12.797
I was her hostage!

11:16.009 --> 11:17.636
Hi, sir.

11:17.677 --> 11:19.179
My name is Jessie.

11:19.180 --> 11:20.680
Clearly there's been

11:17.677 --> 11:20.680
a little mistake here,

11:20.722 --> 11:22.329
so Zuri will just give you

11:22.330 --> 11:23.934
back your Bunny-Poopy-Bot,

11:23.975 --> 11:25.727
- and you give us
- Military Mary.

11:25.769 --> 11:27.187
No way!

11:27.229 --> 11:28.710
Only seven of these dolls

11:28.711 --> 11:30.190
with scars were ever made.

11:30.232 --> 11:32.192
- Which means I'm gonna
- make some money.

11:32.234 --> 11:34.111
Have you no heart?

11:34.152 --> 11:35.217
Jessie's father

11:35.218 --> 11:36.280
gave her that toy!

11:36.321 --> 11:38.783
So what? My mother

11:38.784 --> 11:41.243
gave me an ulcer.

11:36.321 --> 11:41.243
Boo-hoo!

11:41.285 --> 11:42.515
Look, Missy, if you want

11:42.516 --> 11:43.745
your precious doll back,

11:43.787 --> 11:44.872
you can bid on it

11:44.873 --> 11:45.956
at the Toy-tacular,

11:45.997 --> 11:47.041
like the rest of

11:47.042 --> 11:48.083
the pathetic geeks.

11:48.125 --> 11:50.252
Valued customers, I mean.

11:52.379 --> 11:53.338
Wait...

11:53.380 --> 11:54.527
Don't worry, Mary!

11:54.528 --> 11:55.674
We will find you!

11:55.715 --> 11:57.009
Only tell him your name,

11:57.010 --> 11:58.302
rank, and serial number!

11:59.511 --> 12:00.887
She'll be okay.

12:00.929 --> 12:02.035
She has kung fu grip

12:02.036 --> 12:03.140
and fairy dust.

12:08.228 --> 12:09.813
(SALSA MUSIC PLAYING)

12:13.900 --> 12:15.653
- I'm so proud
- of Bertram.

12:15.694 --> 12:17.529
- I can't believe
- he's actually doing it.

12:17.571 --> 12:19.156
The way you dressed him,

12:19.157 --> 12:20.740
I can't believe he actually

12:17.571 --> 12:20.740
left the house.

12:22.742 --> 12:24.244
You are doing wonderfully,

12:24.245 --> 12:25.745
guapo, but you seem

12:22.742 --> 12:25.745
a little nervous.

12:25.787 --> 12:26.934
Nervous?

12:26.935 --> 12:28.081
I'm not nervous.

12:30.875 --> 12:32.210
I'm barely aware

12:32.211 --> 12:33.545
that there are three

12:30.875 --> 12:33.545
incredibly stern judges

12:33.587 --> 12:35.297
watching my every move.

12:36.632 --> 12:37.924
(HICCUPS)

12:37.966 --> 12:39.968
Do not worry.

12:40.010 --> 12:41.220
Now that

12:41.221 --> 12:42.429
they are watching...

12:40.010 --> 12:42.429
Twirl me!

12:42.471 --> 12:43.639
Now? Are you sure?

12:43.640 --> 12:44.806
(HICCUPPING CONTINUES)

12:44.848 --> 12:46.120
We're doing so well with

12:46.121 --> 12:47.392
this "one, two, three" thing.

12:48.893 --> 12:50.562
(HOOTS EXCITEDLY)

12:50.604 --> 12:52.272
- Ooh, here comes
- the twirl!

12:52.314 --> 12:54.232
- Twirl her like
- spaghetti, Bertram!

12:57.068 --> 12:58.403
(EXCLAIMS JOYFULLY)

13:05.661 --> 13:07.601
You have no business

13:07.602 --> 13:09.540
being out on that

13:05.661 --> 13:09.540
dance floor with her!

13:10.415 --> 13:11.833
You stink!

13:11.875 --> 13:13.189
You should've stuck

13:13.190 --> 13:14.503
to making salsa!

13:15.295 --> 13:17.631
Totalmente horrible!

13:17.673 --> 13:19.007
Que lastima.

13:20.592 --> 13:22.302
Quiet, Bertrams!

13:25.305 --> 13:26.536
Bertram,

13:26.537 --> 13:27.766
where are you going?

13:27.807 --> 13:29.559
We are doing the salsa,

13:29.560 --> 13:31.311
not the running man!

13:31.353 --> 13:32.772
What happened?

13:32.773 --> 13:34.189
He was doing so great.

13:34.231 --> 13:35.483
Oh, I knew I shouldn't

13:35.484 --> 13:36.734
have mentioned spaghetti.

13:36.775 --> 13:37.881
He's probably hip deep

13:37.882 --> 13:38.985
in meatballs by now.

13:40.529 --> 13:41.572
We can fix this.

13:41.613 --> 13:43.049
- One of us should go
- wrangle Bertram

13:43.073 --> 13:45.193
- While the other dances
- with his beautiful partner.

13:45.659 --> 13:46.660
Luke?

13:49.747 --> 13:51.582
Hi. I'm Bertram 2.0.

13:51.623 --> 13:53.458
- Congratulations
- on your free upgrade.

13:55.126 --> 13:56.336
Bam!

14:01.800 --> 14:03.115
(PANTS)

14:03.116 --> 14:04.428
Sold out?

14:04.469 --> 14:05.492
It's just a bunch

14:05.493 --> 14:06.513
of old toys,

14:06.555 --> 14:08.306
- not a Blake Shelton
- concert!

14:11.810 --> 14:12.895
I think I found

14:12.896 --> 14:13.978
our way in.

14:11.810 --> 14:13.978
(GASPS)

14:16.106 --> 14:17.357
We fake a neck injury?

14:17.899 --> 14:20.026
No.

14:20.068 --> 14:21.629
- No, we conk those
- Snuggle Bugs on the head,

14:21.653 --> 14:22.801
Take their costumes,

14:22.802 --> 14:23.947
put them in the back

14:21.653 --> 14:23.947
of the Snug-Mobile,

14:23.988 --> 14:25.717
- lock the doors, - hide the keys
- In a dumpster...

14:25.741 --> 14:27.577
Or we could just

14:27.578 --> 14:29.411
take three costumes off

14:25.741 --> 14:29.411
of this unattended rack.

14:30.495 --> 14:31.830
You're no fun.

14:35.751 --> 14:37.669
- Bertram,
- what's going on?

14:37.711 --> 14:38.775
I can't believe

14:38.776 --> 14:39.838
I thought this would work.

14:39.879 --> 14:41.757
- Well, you usually need
- someone to push you.

14:43.425 --> 14:44.694
- I'm not talking
- about the swing,

14:44.718 --> 14:46.012
I'm talking about

14:46.013 --> 14:47.304
the dance contest.

14:47.345 --> 14:48.597
I really thought

14:48.598 --> 14:49.848
I could pull this off.

14:49.889 --> 14:51.036
But all those people

14:51.037 --> 14:52.183
were staring,

14:52.225 --> 14:53.665
and the judges

14:53.666 --> 14:55.103
were so judge-y.

14:55.145 --> 14:56.855
- But you were doing
- great out there.

14:56.896 --> 14:58.523
Really? Was I?

14:58.774 --> 15:00.692
Yes!

15:00.734 --> 15:01.819
You should've seen

15:01.820 --> 15:02.902
how excited Salma was

15:00.734 --> 15:02.902
dancing with you.

15:02.944 --> 15:04.175
She looked like you

15:04.176 --> 15:05.405
the day you got your

15:02.944 --> 15:05.405
new pressure cooker.

15:05.447 --> 15:07.240
That excited?

15:07.282 --> 15:09.618
Yes, that excited.

15:09.660 --> 15:11.578
- Bertram, you've
- worked so hard.

15:11.620 --> 15:13.371
You're a great dancer now.

15:13.413 --> 15:14.956
Salma thinks you can do it,

15:14.998 --> 15:16.875
- Luke and I think
- you can do it.

15:16.916 --> 15:18.501
The only person saying

15:18.502 --> 15:20.086
you can't do it is you.

15:20.128 --> 15:21.401
Well, there were actually

15:21.402 --> 15:22.673
four of me saying it.

15:22.714 --> 15:23.715
Huh?

15:24.299 --> 15:25.676
Long story.

15:26.926 --> 15:28.762
Which there is no time for,

15:28.804 --> 15:30.285
because the girl of your

15:30.286 --> 15:31.765
dreams is waiting for you

15:28.804 --> 15:31.765
on that dance floor,

15:31.807 --> 15:33.725
- and she needs you
- to win this contest!

15:34.726 --> 15:36.087
- You really think
- I can do this?

15:36.770 --> 15:37.979
Yes!

15:38.021 --> 15:39.857
Now, why aren't you moving?

15:39.898 --> 15:40.899
Because I'm stuck

15:40.900 --> 15:41.900
in this swing!

15:43.485 --> 15:44.695
(GRUNTS)

15:44.736 --> 15:46.112
- (EXHALES DEEPLY)
- Let's go.

15:49.658 --> 15:50.784
There's Sneed!

15:51.451 --> 15:52.703
(STATIC)

15:52.744 --> 15:53.767
Attention,

15:53.768 --> 15:54.788
ladies and gentlemen.

15:54.830 --> 15:56.644
Remember to stick around

15:56.645 --> 15:58.458
for the big toy auction

15:54.830 --> 15:58.458
after the show.

15:58.500 --> 16:00.314
The first item up

16:00.315 --> 16:02.128
for bid is a rare

15:58.500 --> 16:02.128
Military Mary doll.

16:02.170 --> 16:03.421
(ALL GASP)

16:03.463 --> 16:04.631
The bidding

16:04.632 --> 16:05.799
will start at $1,000.

16:05.841 --> 16:07.343
(ALL GASP)

16:07.344 --> 16:08.844
ALL: $1,000.

16:08.886 --> 16:10.780
- That makes it - the most expensive
- Thing I own!

16:10.804 --> 16:11.972
I don't want to

16:11.973 --> 16:13.139
split hairs here,

16:13.181 --> 16:14.766
but you did give

16:14.767 --> 16:16.351
the doll to me.

16:16.393 --> 16:18.433
- Do you really want - to bring that up
- Right now?

16:19.062 --> 16:20.814
Jessie, where are you

16:20.815 --> 16:22.566
going to get a $1,000?

16:22.607 --> 16:24.235
They cut up your credit card

16:24.236 --> 16:25.861
at a frozen yogurt stand.

16:25.903 --> 16:27.112
I never should've

16:27.113 --> 16:28.321
splurged on sprinkles.

16:28.363 --> 16:30.114
- Okay, you guys go
- buzz around Sneed,

16:30.156 --> 16:31.992
And I'll grab Mary with

16:31.993 --> 16:33.827
whichever one of these

16:30.156 --> 16:33.827
is my real arm.

16:35.495 --> 16:37.121
Before the bidding begins,

16:37.163 --> 16:38.457
the Snuggle Bugs

16:38.458 --> 16:39.750
will be performing

16:37.163 --> 16:39.750
their hit single,

16:39.791 --> 16:42.001
As Long As You Bug Me.

16:42.043 --> 16:43.921
- JESSIE: - Hey. Wait, wait,
- Wait... What?

16:43.962 --> 16:45.256
Hey, watch it, bro,

16:45.257 --> 16:46.548
keep your feelers

16:43.962 --> 16:46.548
to yourself.

16:51.219 --> 16:53.722
(SALSA MUSIC PLAYING)

16:53.764 --> 16:54.848
Oh, God.

16:54.890 --> 16:56.142
Sorry I cut out.

16:56.143 --> 16:57.392
Can I cut back in?

16:57.434 --> 16:58.602
Sure, we have to

16:58.603 --> 16:59.770
make it look smooth.

16:59.811 --> 17:01.271
Let's do the reverse copa.

17:01.312 --> 17:02.377
Five, six,

17:02.378 --> 17:03.440
seven, eight...

17:11.990 --> 17:13.032
Maybe we should

17:13.034 --> 17:14.075
try that again.

17:11.990 --> 17:14.075
You think?

17:14.117 --> 17:15.827
- Five, six,
- seven, eight.

17:20.915 --> 17:22.001
I'm sorry, Salma.

17:22.002 --> 17:23.084
If you knew me better,

17:23.126 --> 17:24.732
you'd know I typically

17:24.733 --> 17:26.337
don't run away like that.

17:26.378 --> 17:27.964
Or run, period.

17:29.215 --> 17:30.801
- I'm just glad
- you are back.

17:30.842 --> 17:31.865
Your little friend

17:31.866 --> 17:32.886
was a bit of a showboat.

17:37.307 --> 17:38.976
(CROWD CHEERING)

17:42.729 --> 17:44.314
- Luke, we're dancing
- so well,

17:44.355 --> 17:45.420
That all that's left

17:45.421 --> 17:46.483
is us and Bertram.

17:46.524 --> 17:47.630
We have to stop

17:47.631 --> 17:48.735
being so awesome.

17:46.524 --> 17:48.735
(SCOFFS)

17:48.777 --> 17:50.497
- That's like asking me
- to stop breathing.

17:51.237 --> 17:52.280
Is that an option?

17:54.950 --> 17:56.452
Salma, it's time

17:56.453 --> 17:57.953
to win that trophy.

17:57.995 --> 17:59.913
- Maybe we should
- let them win.

17:59.955 --> 18:01.706
They are only children.

18:01.748 --> 18:03.207
- They both have
- giant trust funds,

18:03.249 --> 18:04.668
And they'll never

18:04.669 --> 18:06.085
have to work a day

18:03.249 --> 18:06.085
in their lives.

18:07.754 --> 18:09.088
Let us do this!

18:27.148 --> 18:28.733
(ALL CHEERING)

18:32.696 --> 18:34.635
Bertram,

18:34.636 --> 18:36.574
you were wonderful.

18:36.616 --> 18:37.784
You think that

18:37.785 --> 18:38.952
was good, you should

18:36.616 --> 18:38.952
see me make salsa.

18:41.038 --> 18:42.246
(GASPS)

18:42.789 --> 18:43.874
We did it!

18:43.915 --> 18:45.542
- We did it!
- (CHUCKLES)

18:47.126 --> 18:48.962
They did it? What?

18:49.713 --> 18:51.006
(BERTRAM SIGHS)

18:51.923 --> 18:54.843
I'm really sorry, Salma.

18:54.885 --> 18:56.845
- I know you wanted
- to win that trophy.

18:56.887 --> 18:57.930
Do not be silly,

18:57.931 --> 18:58.972
Bertram.

18:59.014 --> 19:00.057
I got something

19:00.058 --> 19:01.099
much better.

19:01.140 --> 19:03.852
A cute new novio.

19:03.894 --> 19:05.353
You won a car?

19:07.022 --> 19:08.356
No, silly.

19:08.398 --> 19:10.108
Novio means boyfriend.

19:10.149 --> 19:11.943
Oh. (CHUCKLES)

19:11.985 --> 19:13.466
Oh. (CHUCKLES)

19:13.467 --> 19:14.946
Wow.

19:14.988 --> 19:16.428
Sorry, Bertram.

19:16.429 --> 19:17.866
We weren't trying to win,

19:17.908 --> 19:19.160
but when you combine

19:19.161 --> 19:20.410
me with a dance floor

19:17.908 --> 19:20.410
and a crowd,

19:20.451 --> 19:21.828
there's only

19:21.829 --> 19:23.204
so many ways

19:20.451 --> 19:23.204
it can end.

19:23.246 --> 19:24.706
- But we're totes
- proud of you,

19:24.748 --> 19:26.225
- And we really want
- you to have this.

19:26.249 --> 19:28.126
Thanks, but Salma

19:28.127 --> 19:30.003
and I already have

19:26.249 --> 19:30.003
everything we need.

19:30.336 --> 19:32.130
Si, guapo.

19:32.171 --> 19:33.882
(CHUCKLES)

19:33.924 --> 19:34.925
Ugh! Let's get out

19:34.926 --> 19:35.926
of here before she starts

19:33.924 --> 19:35.926
running her fingers

19:35.967 --> 19:37.135
through his scalp.

19:44.851 --> 19:46.913
- JESSIE: Okay, looks like
- we're gonna have to perform.

19:46.937 --> 19:48.063
Just follow my lead

19:48.064 --> 19:49.188
and try to fake your

19:46.937 --> 19:49.188
way through this.

19:49.230 --> 19:50.815
RAVI: Are you kidding?

19:50.857 --> 19:52.442
We have seen every

19:52.443 --> 19:54.027
Snuggle Bugs episode

19:50.857 --> 19:54.027
a zillion times.

19:54.069 --> 19:55.278
ZURI: It's the reason

19:55.279 --> 19:56.487
I have no attention span!

19:58.115 --> 19:59.741
(FUNKY MUSIC PLAYING)

19:59.783 --> 20:01.367
JESSIE: Whoa, whoa.

20:01.409 --> 20:03.036
- Watch out, watch out.
- Hey! Hey! Hey!

20:06.039 --> 20:07.874
- Whoa, okay! That's...
- That's not right.

20:07.916 --> 20:09.709
Uh...

20:09.751 --> 20:11.419
- Kids actually
- watch this stuff?

20:11.461 --> 20:13.046
Whoa. Hey, hey!

20:13.088 --> 20:14.089
Whoa!

20:14.131 --> 20:15.799
(PANTS) Whoa.

20:15.840 --> 20:17.341
Wait. Huh?

20:17.383 --> 20:19.177
(GRUNTS) Stuck...

20:19.218 --> 20:20.887
Whoa!

20:20.929 --> 20:22.097
(ALL GASP)

20:23.181 --> 20:24.432
(CROWD CHEER)

20:24.474 --> 20:25.558
(ALL BOOING)

20:26.643 --> 20:27.727
Get me down.

20:28.019 --> 20:29.187
On it!

20:31.189 --> 20:32.315
Whoa!

20:32.356 --> 20:33.441
(THUD)

20:35.401 --> 20:36.527
Thanks a lot.

20:36.569 --> 20:37.570
My bad.

20:39.322 --> 20:40.407
Stop them!

20:40.408 --> 20:41.491
They're after my doll.

20:41.532 --> 20:42.867
Wait, uh, that's not

20:42.868 --> 20:44.202
your doll, it's Zuri's.

20:44.243 --> 20:45.307
She traded it

20:45.308 --> 20:46.370
fair and square!

20:46.412 --> 20:48.123
- What is fair about
- taking advantage

20:48.165 --> 20:49.291
Of a gullible,

20:49.292 --> 20:50.416
thoughtless little girl?

20:50.458 --> 20:51.918
No offense.

20:52.836 --> 20:54.253
Wait! Stop!

20:54.295 --> 20:55.985
Friends, parents,

20:55.986 --> 20:57.674
Snuggle Bug enthusiasts.

21:01.011 --> 21:02.595
Toys are special.

21:02.637 --> 21:03.827
They're not just

21:03.828 --> 21:05.015
things to buy and sell,

21:05.056 --> 21:06.621
they're part

21:06.622 --> 21:08.185
of our happiest

21:05.056 --> 21:08.185
childhood moments,

21:08.935 --> 21:10.979
our most precious memories.

21:11.021 --> 21:12.105
Preach!

21:14.440 --> 21:15.734
So, we should take

21:15.735 --> 21:17.027
really good care

21:14.440 --> 21:17.027
of our toys,

21:17.068 --> 21:18.800
because at one

21:18.801 --> 21:20.530
time or another,

21:20.571 --> 21:21.865
they took pretty

21:21.866 --> 21:23.158
good care of us.

21:23.200 --> 21:24.722
And this man tricked

21:24.723 --> 21:26.244
my little Zuri

21:26.285 --> 21:28.204
into trading away

21:28.205 --> 21:30.123
my Military Mary

21:26.285 --> 21:30.123
for some cheap Poopy-Bot,

21:30.165 --> 21:31.916
which is already out of poop!

21:31.958 --> 21:33.334
(ALL GASP)

21:33.376 --> 21:34.711
And he lied about

21:34.712 --> 21:36.046
Mary's real value.

21:36.087 --> 21:37.755
(ALL GASP)

21:37.797 --> 21:39.487
And he did not

21:39.488 --> 21:41.176
provide a receipt!

21:41.218 --> 21:43.282
What, no gasps

21:43.283 --> 21:45.346
of indignation at this lack

21:41.218 --> 21:45.346
of common business courtesy?

21:47.224 --> 21:48.391
Come on!

21:48.432 --> 21:49.622
My profit margins

21:49.623 --> 21:50.810
are razor thin.

21:50.852 --> 21:52.603
- If I don't cheat
- your spoiled brats,

21:52.645 --> 21:54.486
- How am I supposed
- to pay for my sports car?

21:56.274 --> 21:57.483
Get him!

21:57.525 --> 21:58.860
(KIDS YELLING)

21:58.902 --> 22:00.487
SNEED: Ow! Mom?

22:00.488 --> 22:02.072
Quit it!

22:02.113 --> 22:04.074
- We should
- get out of here.

22:04.115 --> 22:05.221
Looks like Sneed's about

22:05.222 --> 22:06.325
to get the chocolate

22:04.115 --> 22:06.325
beat out of him.

22:11.455 --> 22:12.603
Aw, Zuri,

22:12.604 --> 22:13.750
you're playing with Mary.

22:13.791 --> 22:15.168
You know you don't have to.

22:15.210 --> 22:16.627
Are you kidding me?

22:16.669 --> 22:18.693
I'm not taking

22:18.694 --> 22:20.715
my eyes off of her.

22:16.669 --> 22:20.715
She's valuable.

22:20.757 --> 22:22.050
Yeah, $1,000

22:22.051 --> 22:23.342
is a lot of cash.

22:24.094 --> 22:25.678
I don't mean the money.

22:25.720 --> 22:27.034
She's valuable because

22:27.035 --> 22:28.347
you gave her to me.

22:29.182 --> 22:30.600
Aw.

22:32.310 --> 22:33.771
Plus, Military Mary

22:33.772 --> 22:35.230
is really fun.

22:35.272 --> 22:36.689
Oh, I know, right?

22:36.731 --> 22:37.921
One time I had her

22:37.922 --> 22:39.109
rescue the president

22:36.731 --> 22:39.109
from evil aliens.

22:39.150 --> 22:40.882
Well, today Mary

22:40.883 --> 22:42.612
is on a secret mission.

22:42.653 --> 22:44.614
- The whole world
- hangs in the balance.

22:49.160 --> 22:50.954
All right, Chubbs.

22:50.995 --> 22:52.205
Tell us where

22:52.206 --> 22:53.414
you hid the honey!

22:53.456 --> 22:55.479
Or fuzzy-wuzzy

22:55.480 --> 22:57.501
won't be so fuzzy.

23:00.504 --> 23:02.215
This brings back

23:02.216 --> 23:03.925
so many happy, childhood

23:00.504 --> 23:03.925
interrogation memories.

